Subject: [ARCHIVED space] Add Hugging Face Space configuration on a branch of
 its own

Spaces reads its configuration from YAML front matter at the top of README.md.
Putting that on master would render as a stray metadata table above the project
README on GitHub, so it lives here instead: this branch is what gets pushed to
the Space, and master stays a document written for a human reader.

The emoji field is Spaces gallery metadata, not an icon in the application. The
app still ships none.
---
 README.md | 15 +++++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 15 insertions(+)

diff --git a/README.md b/README.md
index db7be78..f8a5d19 100644
--- a/README.md
+++ b/README.md
@@ -1,3 +1,18 @@
+---
+title: SaafSaans
+emoji: 🌫️
+colorFrom: blue
+colorTo: gray
+sdk: docker
+app_port: 7860
+pinned: false
+short_description: Delhi air quality, scored for your body, in plain language
+---
+
+<!-- The block above is Hugging Face Spaces configuration and exists only on this
+     branch. `master` and `v1-closure` stay clean. The emoji is Spaces metadata
+     for its gallery card, not an icon in the application, which ships none. -->
+
 # SaafSaans — Delhi Air Quality & Public Health Companion
 
